                <article class="bd-article">
                  
  <section id="features">
<h1>Features<a class="headerlink" href="#features" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h1>
<section id="login">
<h2>Login<a class="headerlink" href="#login" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h2>
<p>The Data Wallet allows users to log in using an identity provider (IDP) configured at build time and follows the <a class="reference external" href="https://solidproject.org/TR/oidc-primer">Solid OIDC</a> flow.</p>
<p>The default IDP for PodSpaces will be <a class="reference external" href="https://login.inrupt.com/">https://login.inrupt.com/</a>. After logging in, the user is taken to the home tab.</p>
</section>
<section id="home">
<h2>Home<a class="headerlink" href="#home" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h2>
<section id="managing-data-in-the-wallet">
<h3>Managing Data in the Wallet<a class="headerlink" href="#managing-data-in-the-wallet" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h3>
<p>Users are able to browse and manage the contents of their Wallet on the Home tab.</p>
<section id="adding-data-to-the-wallet">
<h4>Adding Data to the Wallet<a class="headerlink" href="#adding-data-to-the-wallet" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h4>
<p>The Add function allows users to upload data to the Wallet from the phone file system, the photo library, or by taking a photo with the camera.</p>
<a class="reference internal image-reference" href="../_images/adding-data-to-the-wallet.png"><img alt="Adding data to the Wallet" src="../_images/adding-data-to-the-wallet.png" style="width: 300px;" />
</a>
<div class="admonition note">
<p class="admonition-title">Note</p>
<p>The ESS Wallet Service restricts the size of resources uploaded to 10MB. Resources larger than this limit will not be uploaded.</p>
</div>
<section id="file">
<h5>File<a class="headerlink" href="#file" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h5>
<p>When File is selected, the OS File browser is opened. Users can select a file from their file system and the file is uploaded to the Wallet.</p>
</section>
<section id="photo">
<h5>Photo<a class="headerlink" href="#photo" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h5>
<p>When Photo is selected, the OS Photo gallery is opened. Users can select a photo from their photo library and the photo is uploaded to the Wallet.</p>
</section>
<section id="camera">
<h5>Camera<a class="headerlink" href="#camera" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h5>
<p>When Camera is selected, the OS camera is started. Users can take a photo with their phone camera and the photo is uploaded to the Wallet.</p>
</section>
<section id="scan">
<h5>Scan<a class="headerlink" href="#scan" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h5>
<p>Users can use the Scan function to scan a QR code and download a resource, such as a verifiable credential, image, binary file, or cryptographic key, and store it in the Wallet.
The QR code must contain details of the resource to be downloaded. For example:</p>
<div class="highlight-JSON notranslate"><div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="p">{</span>
<span class="w">   </span><span class="nt">&quot;uri&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="s2">&quot;https://storage.example/data/MyImage&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span>
<span class="w">   </span><span class="nt">&quot;contentType&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="s2">&quot;image/png&quot;</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</section>
</section>
</section>
<section id="viewing-data-in-the-wallet">
<h3>Viewing data in the Wallet<a class="headerlink" href="#viewing-data-in-the-wallet" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h3>
<p>On the Home tab, selecting a resource will display its content as follows:</p>
<p>If the file is a W3C Verifiable Credential, it is opened and the following information from the VC is displayed:</p>
<ul class="simple">
<li><p>The claim, the metadata, and an icon showing the revocation status.</p></li>
<li><p>The signature of the credential will be checked and the revocation list obtained will need to be obtained to validate the credential.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>If the file is a Photo, it is opened and displayed.</p>
<p>If the file is not in a supported image format or a credential, it will not be opened or displayed, however, the Actions menu will open so the user can choose an action to take, such as downloading it to the device or deleting it from the Wallet.</p>
<section id="actions-menu">
<h4>Actions Menu<a class="headerlink" href="#actions-menu" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h4>
<p>Users can use the three-dots menu icon next to each resource to display a number of options.</p>
<a class="reference internal image-reference" href="../_images/actions-menu.png"><img alt="Actions menu" src="../_images/actions-menu.png" style="width: 300px;" />
</a>
<section id="share-resource-via-access-grant-qr-code">
<h5>Share Resource via Access Grant QR code<a class="headerlink" href="#share-resource-via-access-grant-qr-code" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h5>
<p>A resource can be shared via a QR code. The QR code contains a JSON object with all the information required to generate an Access Request for this resource, including:</p>
<ul class="simple">
<li><p>WebID</p></li>
<li><p>Resource location</p></li>
</ul>
<p>For example:</p>
<div class="highlight-JSON notranslate"><div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="p">{</span>
<span class="w">    </span><span class="nt">&quot;webId&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="s2">&quot;https://www.example.com/id&quot;</span><span class="p">,</span>
<span class="w">    </span><span class="nt">&quot;resource&quot;</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="s2">&quot;https://storage.example/wallet/IMG_0005.jpg&quot;</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</section>
<section id="download-a-copy">
<h5>Download a copy<a class="headerlink" href="#download-a-copy" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h5>
<p>The OS Share menu is opened, and the user can select to save to device or cloud storage, or share the resource with available applications.</p>
</section>
<section id="delete">
<h5>Delete<a class="headerlink" href="#delete" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h5>
<p>The user is presented with an alert to confirm deletion. On confirmation, the resource is removed from the Wallet. All Access Requests associated with the resource are deleted from the Requests tab. All Access Grants associated with the resource are revoked.</p>
</section>
</section>
</section>
</section>
<section id="profile">
<h2>Profile<a class="headerlink" href="#profile" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h2>
<p>This tab displays the profile information of the Wallet owner.</p>
<p>Users can see their WebID, name, and profile picture (if set). A QR code is also provided which can be used to share the user’s WebID. Additionally, users can logout from this tab using the three-dots menu icon.</p>
<section id="sharing-users-digital-identity">
<h3>Sharing User’s Digital Identity<a class="headerlink" href="#sharing-users-digital-identity" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h3>
<p>The Wallet displays the user’s WebID as a QR code. This can be used to create an Access Request.</p>
<p>Applications can scan the QR code in order to obtain the WebID. Once they have the WebID they can locate the inbox associated with the Wallet and use this to create Access Requests for data stored within it. Access Requests must be approved by the Wallet holder before data can be accessed.</p>
<a class="reference internal image-reference" href="../_images/profile.png"><img alt="Profile view" src="../_images/profile.png" style="width: 300px;" />
</a>
</section>
</section>
<section id="requests">
<h2>Requests<a class="headerlink" href="#requests" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h2>
<p>This tab shows all pending Access Requests the user has received for data inside the Wallet.
From here, the user can view request details, such as requester, access mode, the name of the resource and the access expiry date. The user can choose to Confirm or Deny the request. If the user confirms, the requester will be granted the specified access mode (such as read or write) to the resource.</p>
<a class="reference internal image-reference" href="../_images/requests.png"><img alt="Requests list" src="../_images/requests.png" style="width: 300px;" />
</a>
</section>
<section id="access">
<h2>Access<a class="headerlink" href="#access" title="Link to this heading">#</a></h2>
<p>This tab shows what access has been granted to other agents.</p>
<p>For each agent, there is a list of the Wallet resources they have been approved access. Users have the option to revoke access to specific resources, or revoke all access from the agent.</p>
<a class="reference internal image-reference" href="../_images/access.png"><img alt="Accessible resources list" src="../_images/access.png" style="width: 300px;" />
</a>
</section>
</section>


                </article>
              


              
              
              
              
